-1.title: Episode dated 29 April 2014
-1.plot: A TV sports producer who's looking to buy a lake house in CT, can't move forward until her agents sell her Chelsea home. The agents have face-to-face meetings with top brokers to hard-sell the merits of the property.

1.title: The Big Event
1.plot: Two NYC luxury real estate agencies plan big events to sell their multi-million dollar properties.

2.title: Time Is Money!
2.plot: The inside story of NYC real estate agents as they sell million dollar apartments on a deadline.

4.plot: A look at the lengths top NYC realtors go to, in order to make their affluent clients happy.

5.plot: Manhattan agents help clients invest in multi-million-dollar properties.

6.plot: NYC realtors come to the rescue of struggling family members and their multi-million dollar deals.

7.plot: NYC agents sell unbelievable multi-million dollar homes, from the Upper West Side to Soho.

8.plot: NYC agents go the extra mile to attract and keep valued clients; touring Boca Raton and the Big Apple.

9.title: Managing Expectations: NYC Agents Negotiate Clients and Their High Expectations
9.plot: Top Manhattan real estate agents negotiate clients and their lofty expectations

10.title: Property Hunters: Two Agents Set Forth to Find Sound Investments for Their Clients
10.plot: Two NYC agents hunt for the perfect investment properties in Brooklyn and the Hamptons.

11.plot: Competing real estate firms strive to satisfy their clients under tight deadlines.

12.plot: Core's reputation is on the line while the Kleiers' take on a couple with two distinct visions.

13.title: Glamour and High Business: Two Agencies Attempt to Lure Millionaire Buyers
13.plot: Two real estate agencies attempt to lure millionaire buyers for luxury Manhattan properties.

1.title: Developing a Deal
1.plot: NYC real estate brokers try to impress developers by selling million-dollar apartments fast!

2.title: Smells Like a Deal!
2.plot: Core broker Tom Postilio thinks outside of the box in order to sell two luxury apartments located across the street from a city sanitation facility. Meanwhile, Warburg agent Deborah Lupard takes on a soap star's authentic Tribeca listing and discovers the loft's private rooftop space is a harder sell than expected.

3.title: Getting the Buy In
3.plot: Veteran Gumley Haft Kleier broker John Mehigan lands an exclusive and unique property: a private island home, an hour outside the city. But finding the right buyer will be like finding a needle in a haystack. Meanwhile, Michael Graves of Core needs to attract the right buyer for a Park Avenue apartment with unseen potential. He decides to hold an event of a different kind to get eyes on the listing.

4.title: The Price Is Right
4.plot: A design-savvy couple entrusts the sale of their Williamsburg townhouse to Core agent Doug Bowen, in order to relocate to California. Meanwhile, Gumley Haft Kleier agent Bruce Cohen tries to avoid wasting time on a client and friend who may have spent too much time away from the city, and is out of touch with the Manhattan market.

5.title: Real Estate, Friends & Neighbors
5.plot: Broker Samantha Kleier works with her best friend, who's torn between staying in the city and moving to the 'suburbs; while agent Deborah Lupard tries her hardest to convince a client that he needs to move in to his newly purchased Financial District apartment ? not put it up for sale before giving the neighborhood a try.

6.title: Dream Homes
6.plot: Top NYC brokers discover it's not always easy to find wealthy clients the next home of their dreams.

7.title: Launch Pad
7.plot: Core agent Maggie Kent works with a new client whose looking to upgrade from his one bedroom co-op so he can spend more time in Manhattan. Over on the West Coast, Warburg broker Richard Steinberg partners with a Los Angeles agent in order to help a dear friend find the perfect L.A. pad.

8.title: Big City Dreams
8.plot: When Nashville based country star Clay Walker wants a place to hang his hat in New York City, Samantha Kleier gets the referral. However, she must help her client get over the sticker shock, or risk losing more high profile referrals from ex-boss and publicist Susan Blond. Meanwhile, Warburg agent Deborah Lupard has her own out-of-town client to educate - a San Francisco-based artist who wants a spacious live/work space in a trendy neighborhood that doesn't break the bank.

9.title: Hot Property!
9.plot: In their summer downtime, one top broker looks for a new agent and another hunts for a vacation rental.

10.title: Positive Change
10.plot: To sell an impressive $6.75-million listing in a controversial building, Warburg broker Richard Steinberg manages opposing visions as a professional stager and Feng Shui find themselves at odds. Meanwhile, the Kleiers negotiate between a mother and daughter who disagree on the need for a doorman, but may see the value in buying over renting.

11.title: Home Improvements
11.plot: In an effort to impress a foreign investor and ensure future business, Warburg broker Leslie Modell Rosenthal must convince him to invest in an $150,000 reno in order to sell his outdated condo quickly. But when unexpected problems arise, Leslie worries that her promise to keep the work on time and on budget may fall short. Across town, to sell a rundown Park Avenue apartment, Core agent Elizabeth Kee believes her client must spend money to improve its first impression or drop the price dramatically. When the answer is no to both suggestions, the young agent must get ...

12.title: Starter Homes
12.plot: Top NYC agents guide inexperienced property hunters toward making the right real estate decisions.

13.title: Demanding Attention
13.plot: Gumley Haft Kleier broker Laurel Rosenbluth deals with a one-of-a-kind listing that's bound to attract interest, but to make sure it's the right kind, she needs to find the right listing price. And Warburg agent Leslie Modell Rosenthal deals with a stressed out client, whose downsizing dreams of moving to Florida are hindering her ability to commit to buying a New York pied-a-terre.

1.title: Deal Or No Deal
1.plot: Broker Samantha Kleier-Forbes helps two newlyweds decide between renting and buying when their expanding brood outgrows their current digs. And Warburg broker Deborah Lupard gets frustrated when her celebrity client waffles over a rental.

2.title: Market the Place
2.plot: NYC brokers and agents get creative in marketing their unique listings.

3.title: Teaming With Sales
3.plot: Warburg broker Leslie Modell Rosenthal calls on a colleague to help her make a sale in unfamiliar territory. And Core broker Kirk Rundhaug rallies his troupes to try and sell two units which could lead to a penthouse listing if sold successfully.

4.title: Property Values
4.plot: The Kleiers don kid gloves when they attempt to negotiate the right asking price with determined sellers. And Warburg's Richard Steinberg mixes business with pleasure when he agrees to help a family friend.

5.title: Property Virgin
5.plot: Warburg broker Leslie Modell Rosenthal works with an indecisive client who also happens to be her daughter's boyfriend. And new GHK agent, Curtis Nixon, endeavors to find a first time buyer the perfect home on an imperfect budget.

6.title: Above and Beyond
6.plot: Two NYC brokers go to great lengths for their clients.

7.title: All Eyes On It
7.plot: Luxury listings land two of NY's top brokers on real estate's watch list.

8.title: Hard Sell
8.plot: Warburg's Richard Steinberg must convince his developer clients that he has both the influence and creativity to sell a luxury penthouse listing. And broker Maggie Kent works hard to persuade a seller to list a unique town home with Core.

9.title: Growing Pains
9.plot: An agent helps bridge a couple's conflicting opinions about the perfect pad.

10.title: Sales Partners
10.plot: Michele Kleier teams up with a Florida property developer to sell luxury oceanfront apartments in Boca Raton, throwing a party that draws high-profile figures; a pair of agents hold an open house in order to speed up the sale of a Brooklyn apartment.

11.title: Seeing is Believing
11.plot: Young agent John Harrison takes advice from Core's Maggie Kent when his young and inexperienced client's offer is outbid. Veteran broker Laurel Rosenbluth partners with rookie Stephanie Balint to scout apartments on behalf of LA clients who are relocating to the city, but don't have the time to apartment hunt.

12.title: Finders Keepers
12.plot: Warburg's Deborah Lupard finds HGTV Executive Loren Ruch the perfect crash pad for the contestants of a new season of Design Star. Sabrina Kleier-Morgenstern helps her client make a big transition from Bermuda to Manhattan, in order to be closer to her family.

13.title: Moving Deadlines
13.plot: An agent helps a couple see eye to eye, another meets a developer's wish.

imdb.plot outline: In New York City the average price of a home is $2 million plus. This series gives you a glimpse into the lives of buyers, sellers and the brokers. Competition is is stiff, but these realtors are roaring to go. You will see many high profile clientele and celebrities too.
